            <p>
              A personal loan is an unsecured loan that provides you with a lump sum of money, which
              you repay in fixed monthly installments over a set period. These loans can be used for
              various purposes, such as debt consolidation, home improvements, medical expenses, or
              major purchases.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How do personal loans work?</summary>
            <p>
              Once approved, you receive the loan amount in a single payment. You then repay the
              loan in equal monthly installments that cover both the principal and interest, over
              the agreed-upon term.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>What can I use a personal loan for?</summary>
            <p>
              Personal loans are versatile and can be used for consolidating high-interest debts,
              funding home renovations, covering medical bills, financing weddings or vacations, and
              managing unexpected expenses.
            </p>
          </details>

