              rates range from around 6% to 36% APR. Borrowers with excellent credit scores often
              qualify for lower rates.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Will applying for a personal loan affect my credit score?</summary>
            <p>
              Checking your rates through a prequalification process usually involves a soft credit
              inquiry, which doesn't impact your credit score. However, submitting a full
              application may result in a hard inquiry, which can temporarily lower your score by a
